1
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:06,040
(BIRDS TWEETING)

2
00:00:12,680 --> 00:00:15,840
(CROWS CAW)

3
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:25,520
It's a beautiful day.

4
00:00:33,160 --> 00:00:35,240
Hallucinogenic lipstick.

5
00:00:37,280 --> 00:00:39,560
She's here.

6
00:01:02,760 --> 00:01:06,080
(GUN POWERS UP)

7
00:01:08,400 --> 00:01:11,880
(CRACKLING)

8
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:17,000
Wrong. Wrong.

9
00:01:17,080 --> 00:01:18,960
Bit right, mostly wrong.

10
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:20,800
I love museums!

11
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:22,600
Yeah, great(!) Can we go to a planet now?

12
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:25,800
A big spaceship, Churchill's bunker...?
You promised me a planet next.

13
00:01:25,880 --> 00:01:28,480
Amy, this isn't any old asteroid.
It's the Delerium Archive,

14
00:01:28,560 --> 00:01:32,840
the final resting place of the headless
monks, the biggest museum ever.

15
00:01:32,920 --> 00:01:35,000
You've got a time machine.
What do you need museums for?

16
00:01:35,080 --> 00:01:37,080
Wrong! Very wrong!

17
00:01:37,160 --> 00:01:39,160
Oooh, one of mine. Also one of mine.

18
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:43,560
Oh, I see. It's how you keep score.

19
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:56,240
Oh, great, an old box(!)

20
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:05,760
It's from one of the old starliners.
A Home Box.

21
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:07,640
What's a Home Box?

22
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:10,000
Like a black box on a plane,
except it homes.

23
00:02:10,080 --> 00:02:11,720
Anything happens to the ship,

24
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:15,040
the Home Box flies home
with all the flight data.

25
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:16,880
So?

26
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:19,280
The writing, the graffiti -
Old High Gallifreyan.

27
00:02:19,360 --> 00:02:21,840
The lost language of the Time Lords.

28
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:29,880
There were days, there were many days,

29
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:35,640
these words could burn stars
and raise up empires, and topple gods.

30
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:36,680
What does it say?

31
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:42,000
"Hello, sweetie!"

32
00:02:52,360 --> 00:02:53,760
(ALARM BELL RINGING)

33
00:03:10,960 --> 00:03:12,920
Party's over, Doctor Song.

34
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,000
Why are we doing this?

35
00:03:15,120 --> 00:03:18,880
Cos someone on a spaceship 12,000 years
ago is trying to attract my attention.

36
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:22,080
Let's see if we can get
the security playback working.

37
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:36,400
The party's over, Doctor Song,
yet still you're on board.

38
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:43,720
(SHE LAUGHS) Sorry, Alistair.
I needed to see what was in your vault.

39
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:48,160
Do you all know what's down there?
Any of you?

40
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:53,920
Because I'll tell you something.
This ship won't reach its destination.

41
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:58,240
Wait till she runs.
Don't make it look like an execution.

42
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:03,720
Triple-seven, five, slash,
three, four, nine by ten.

43
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:08,040
Zero, twelve, slash, acorn.
Oh, and I could do with an air corridor.

44
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:11,840
- What was that, what did she say?
- Co-ordinates!

45
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:14,560
Like I said on the dance floor,

46
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:19,080
you might want to find something
to hang on to!

47
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:22,120
(BEEPING)

48
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:41,440
WWhoo!

49
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,000
Doctor?

50
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:53,200
River?

51
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:54,920
Follow that ship!

52
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:45,000
They've gone into warp drive.
We're losing them!

53
00:05:45,080 --> 00:05:46,920
- Stay close!
- I'm trying!

54
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,520
Use the stabilisers.

55
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:50,160
There aren't stabilisers!

56
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,240
The blue switches!

57
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:53,760
The blue ones don't do anything,
they're just...blue.

58
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:55,200
Yes, they're blue.

59
00:05:55,280 --> 00:05:58,840
They're the blue stabilisers!

60
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:04,200
See?

61
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:09,880
Yeah, well, it's just boring now,
isn't it? They're boring-ers.

62
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:12,080
They're blue boring-ers.

63
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:15,080
Doctor, how come she can fly the TARDIS?

64
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:17,840
You call that flying the TARDIS? Ha!

65
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:22,240
OK. I've mapped the probability vectors,

66
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:24,760
done a fold-back on the temporal isometry,

67
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:27,680
charted the ship to its destination,

68
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:31,480
and...parked us right alongside.

69
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:34,400
Parked us? We haven't landed.

70
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:37,640
Of course we've landed. I just landed her.

71
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:40,800
But it didn't make the noise.

72
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:43,680
- What noise?
- You know, the...

73
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:45,920
(HE IMPERSONATES TARDIS)

74
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:51,760
It's not supposed to make that noise.
You leave the brakes on.

75
00:06:51,840 --> 00:06:53,640
Yeah, well, it's a brilliant noise.

76
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:54,960
I love that noise.

77
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:58,400
Come along, Pond, let's have a look.

78
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:03,720
- No, wait! Environment checks.
- Oh, yes, sorry! Quite right.

79
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,480
Environment checks.

80
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:09,280
Nice out.

81
00:07:09,360 --> 00:07:12,280
We're somewhere in the Garn Belt.
There's an atmosphere.

82
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:13,440
Early indications suggest...

83
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:16,600
We're on Alfava Metraxis,
the seventh planet of the Dundra System.

84
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:20,800
Oxygen-rich atmosphere, toxins
in the soft band, 11-hour day, and...

85
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:24,080
...chances of rain later.

86
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:26,760
He thinks he's so hot when he does that.

87
00:07:26,840 --> 00:07:28,560
How come you can fly the TARDIS?

88
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:32,800
- Oh, I had lessons from the very best.
- Well, yeah.

89
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:36,080
It's a shame you were busy that day.

90
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:39,520
Right, then, why did they land here?

91
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:42,680
They didn't land.

92
00:07:42,760 --> 00:07:44,560
Sorry?

93
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:48,640
You should've checked the Home Box -
it crashed.

94
00:07:57,720 --> 00:08:00,800
Explain! Who is that
and how did she do that museum thing?

95
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:03,840
It's a long story and I don't know
most of it. Off we go.

96
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:04,920
- What are you doing?
- Leaving.

97
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,080
She's got where she wants to go,

98
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,560
- let's go where we want to go.
- Are you basically running away?

99
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:09,560
- Yep.
- Why?

100
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:11,520
- Cos she's my future.
- Can you run away from that?

101
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:14,200
I can run away from anything I like.
Time is not the boss of me.

102
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:17,520
- Hang on, is that a planet out there?
- Yes, of course it's a planet.

103
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:21,000
You promised me a planet. Five minutes?

104
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:25,120
- OK, five minutes!
- Yes!

105
00:08:25,200 --> 00:08:28,120
But that's all, cos I'm telling you now,

106
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:31,600
that woman is not dragging me
into anything!

107
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,240
What caused it to crash? Not me.

108
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:53,640
Nah, the airlock would've sealed
seconds after you blew it.

109
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:57,200
According to the Home Box,
the warp engines had a phase-shift.

110
00:08:57,280 --> 00:08:58,520
No survivors.

111
00:08:58,600 --> 00:09:01,040
A phase-shift would have to be sabotage.
I did warn them.

112
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:03,720
About what?

113
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:05,800
Well, at least the building was empty.
Aplan temple.

114
00:09:05,880 --> 00:09:08,720
Unoccupied for centuries.

115
00:09:10,760 --> 00:09:13,000
Aren't you going to introduce us?

116
00:09:15,560 --> 00:09:18,160
Amy Pond, Professor River Song.

117
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:21,880
(GASPS) I'm going to be a professor
some day, am I?

118
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:24,240
How exciting!

119
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:26,880
(LAUGHS) Spoilers!

120
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:29,160
Yeah, but who is she
and how did she do that?

121
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:31,080
She just left you a note in a museum.

122
00:09:31,160 --> 00:09:33,840
Two things always guaranteed
to turn up in a museum.

123
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:39,280
The Home Box of category-four star liner
and, sooner or later, him.

124
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:42,240
- It's how he keeps score.
- I know!

125
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:44,080
It's hilarious, isn't it?

126
00:09:44,160 --> 00:09:48,360
I'm nobody's taxi service!
I'm not going to be there to catch you

127
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:52,120
every time you feel like
jumping out of a spaceship.

128
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:54,360
And you are so wrong.

129
00:09:55,680 --> 00:09:59,000
There's one survivor.

130
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:02,720
There's a thing in the belly
of that ship that can't ever die.

131
00:10:09,080 --> 00:10:12,080
Now he's listening. You lot in orbit yet?

132
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:14,320
Yeah, I saw it land.
I'm at the crash site.

133
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:16,720
Try and home in on my signal.

134
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:19,880
Doctor, can you sonic me?

135
00:10:19,960 --> 00:10:23,400
I need to boost the signal
so we can use it as a beacon.

136
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:29,040
Ooh, Doctor! You soniced her(!)

137
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:31,880
We have a minute. Shall we?

138
00:10:31,960 --> 00:10:34,320
Where are we up to?

139
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:37,040
- Have we done the Bone Meadows?
- What's the book?

140
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,160
Stay away from it.

141
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:41,560
- What is it, though?
- Her diary.

142
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:44,880
- Ourdiary.
- Her past, my.. future.

143
00:10:46,720 --> 00:10:50,360
Time travel.
We keep meeting in the wrong order.

144
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:06,160
You promised me an army, Dr Song.

145
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:11,920
No. I promised you the equivalent
of an army. This is the Doctor.

146
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:17,160
Father Octavian, sir. Bishop, second
class. 20 clerics at my command.

147
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:20,080
The troops are already in the drop ship
and landing shortly.

148
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:22,840
Dr Song was helping us
with a covert investigation.

149
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:28,960
Has Dr Song explained
what we're dealing with?

150
00:11:29,040 --> 00:11:34,320
Doctor, what do you know
of the Weeping Angels?

151
00:11:36,920 --> 00:11:40,240
The Angel, as far as we know,
is still trapped in the ship.

152
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:42,720
Our mission is to get inside
and neutralise it.

153
00:11:42,800 --> 00:11:45,880
We can't get through up top,
we'd be too close to the drives.

154
00:11:46,960 --> 00:11:49,680
According to this, behind the cliff face,

155
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:53,680
there's a network of catacombs
leading right up to the temple.

156
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:55,840
We can blow through
the base of the cliffs,

157
00:11:55,920 --> 00:11:58,800
get into the entrance chamber,
then work our way up.

158
00:11:58,880 --> 00:12:00,920
- Oh, good.
- Good, sir?

159
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:03,800
Catacombs, probably dark ones.
Dark catacombs, great(!)

160
00:12:03,880 --> 00:12:07,240
Technically, I think it's called
a maze of the dead.

161
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:09,560
You can stop any time you like.

162
00:12:09,640 --> 00:12:12,280
- Father Octavian?
- Excuse me, sir.

163
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:19,200
You're letting people call you "sir".
You never do that.

164
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:25,400
So whatever a Weeping Angel is,
it's really bad, yeah?

165
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:28,120
Now, that's interesting.

166
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:31,280
You're still here. Which part of "Wait
in the TARDIS till I tell you it's safe”

167
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:34,680
- was so confusing?
- Ooh, are you all Mr Grumpy Face today?

168
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:37,760
A Weeping Angel, Amy, is the deadliest,

169
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:40,920
most powerful, most malevolent
life form evolution has ever produced,

170
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:42,880
and one is trapped inside that wreckage

171
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:45,360
and I'm supposed to climb in
with a screwdriver and a torch,

172
00:12:45,440 --> 00:12:47,160
and assuming I survive the radiation,

173
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:49,320
and the whole ship
doesn't blow up in my face,

174
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:51,760
do something clever
which I haven't thought of yet.

175
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:55,120
That's my day, that's what I'm up to.
Any questions?

176
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:56,600
Is River Song your wife?

177
00:12:56,680 --> 00:13:00,480
Cos she's someone from your future,
and the way she talks to you,

178
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:03,040
I've never seen anyone do that.

179
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:05,560
She's kinda like, you know, "Heel, boy!"

180
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:08,800
She's Mrs Doctor from the future,
isn't she?

181
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:12,320
- Is she going to be your wife one day?
- Yes.

182
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:19,680
You're right.
I am definitely Mr Grumpy Face today.

183
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:21,720
RIVER SONG: Doctor! Doctor!

184
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:25,040
Oops! Her indoors!

185
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:26,280
Father Octavian?

186
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:30,080
Why do they call him "Father"?

187
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:32,480
He's their bishop, they're his clerics.

188
00:13:32,560 --> 00:13:35,480
It's the 51st century,
the Church has moved on.

189
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:51,400
What do you think? It's from the
security cameras in the Byzantium vault.

190
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:54,320
I ripped it when I was on board.
Sorry about the quality.

191
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:56,680
- It's four seconds. I've put it on loop.
- Yep. It's an Angel.

192
00:13:56,800 --> 00:14:01,440
- Hands covering its face.
- You've encountered the Angels before?

193
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:04,160
Once, on Earth, a long time ago. But
those were scavengers, barely surviving.

194
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:06,200
But it's just a statue.

195
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:08,640
- It's a statue when you see it.
- Where did it come from?

196
00:14:08,720 --> 00:14:11,200
Oh, pulled from the ruins
of Razbahan, end of last century.

197
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:14,400
It's been in private hands ever since,
dormant all that time.

198
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:17,800
There's a difference
between dormant and patient.

199
00:14:17,880 --> 00:14:20,760
What does that mean,
it's a statue when you see it?

200
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:25,400
The Weeping Angels can only move
if they're unseen. So legend has it.

201
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:28,040
No, it's not legend. It's a quantum lock.

202
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:32,160
In the sight of any living creature,
the Angels literally cease to exist.

203
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:35,520
They're just stone.
The ultimate defence mechanism.

204
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:37,360
What, being a stone?

205
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:41,720
Being a stone...until you turn your back.

206
00:14:45,800 --> 00:14:47,600
The hyperdrive would've split open
on impact.

207
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:50,800
The whole ship will be flooded
with radiation, cracked electrons,

208
00:14:50,880 --> 00:14:53,120
gravity storms,
deadly to almost any living thing.

209
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,160
Deadly to an Angel?

210
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:57,680
Dinner to an Angel. The longer
we leave it, the stronger it will grow.

211
00:14:57,760 --> 00:14:58,880
Who built that temple?
Are they still around?

212
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:03,360
The Aplans. Indigenous life form.
Died out 400 years ago.

213
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:05,360
200 years later,
the planet was terraformed.

214
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:08,320
Currently there are
six billion human colonists.

215
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:12,480
You lot, you're everywhere! Like rabbits!
I'll never get done saving you.

216
00:15:12,560 --> 00:15:15,200
Sir, if there is a clear and present
danger to the local population...

217
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:19,920
Oh, there is. Bad as it gets.
Bishop, lock and load!

218
00:15:20,040 --> 00:15:24,040
Verger, how are we doing
with those explosives? Dr Song, with me.

219
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:27,480
- Two minutes. Sweetie, I need you.
- (HE MOUTHS)

220
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:30,720
Anybody need me? Nobody?

221
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:48,320
I found this.
Definitive work on the Angels.

222
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:51,720
Well, the only one.
Written by a madman, it's barely readable,

223
00:15:51,800 --> 00:15:54,000
- but I've marked a few passages.
- Not bad, bit slow in the middle,

224
00:15:54,080 --> 00:15:56,760
didn't you hate his girlfriend?
No, hang on, wait, wait!

225
00:15:56,840 --> 00:16:01,480
Dr Song? Did you have
more than one clip of the Angel?

226
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:03,480
No, just the four seconds.

227
00:16:03,560 --> 00:16:07,600
This book is wrong. What's wrong
with this book? It's wrong.

228
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:37,880
It's so strange when you go
all baby-face. How early is this for you?

229
00:16:37,960 --> 00:16:39,400
Very early.

230
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:41,720
So you don't know who I am yet?

231
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:44,440
How do you know who I am?
I don't always look the same.

232
00:16:44,520 --> 00:16:45,960
I've got pictures of all your faces.

233
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:49,800
You never show up in the right order,
though. I need the spotter's guide.

234
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:52,320
Pictures? Why aren't there pictures?

235
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:29,960
You're just a recording. You can't move.

236
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:41,560
(SHE GASPS)

237
00:17:51,120 --> 00:17:52,480
Doctor!

238
00:17:58,440 --> 00:18:00,800
Doctor!

239
00:18:00,880 --> 00:18:03,320
This whole book - it's a warning
about the Weeping Angels.

240
00:18:03,440 --> 00:18:05,200
So why no pictures?
Why not show us what to look out for?

241
00:18:05,280 --> 00:18:07,880
There was a bit about images.
What was that?

242
00:18:07,960 --> 00:18:09,920
Yes! Hang on...

243
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:13,840
"That which holds the image
of an angel becomes itself an angel.”

244
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:20,200
Doctor!

245
00:18:20,280 --> 00:18:25,720
What does that mean? "An image
of a Angel becomes itself an Angel.”

246
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,840
Doctor! It's in the room!

247
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:33,000
- Amy!
- Doctor!

248
00:18:33,080 --> 00:18:36,680
Are you all right? What's happening?

249
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:40,400
Doctor! Doctor, it's coming
out of the television. The Angel is here.

250
00:18:40,520 --> 00:18:42,720
Don't take your eyes off it! Keep
looking. It can't move if you're looking.

251
00:18:42,800 --> 00:18:44,680
- What's wrong?
- Deadlocked.

252
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:46,720
- There is no deadlock.
- Don't even blink, Amy!

253
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:47,720
Doctor!

254
00:18:47,800 --> 00:18:50,480
- What are you doing?
- Cutting the power.

255
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:53,280
It's using the screen,
I'm turning the screen off.

256
00:18:53,360 --> 00:18:56,920
- It's deadlocked the whole system.
- There's no deadlock.

257
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,880
- There is now.
- Help me!

258
00:18:58,960 --> 00:19:00,040
- Can you turn it off?
- Doctor!

259
00:19:00,120 --> 00:19:02,600
- The screen, can you turn it off?
- I tried.

260
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:03,880
Try again, but don't take your eyes
off the Angel.

261
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:06,480
I'm not!

262
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:09,080
If something moves,
it'll move faster. Don't even blink.

263
00:19:10,120 --> 00:19:13,240
I'm not blinking!
Have you ever tried not blinking?

264
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:32,720
- It just keeps switching it back on!
- Yeah, it's the Angel.

265
00:19:33,720 --> 00:19:35,160
But it's just a recording.

266
00:19:35,240 --> 00:19:40,680
No, anything that takes
the image of an Angel ls an Angel.

267
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:43,160
What are you doing?

268
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:44,360
I'm trying to cut through.
It's not even warm.

269
00:19:44,440 --> 00:19:46,480
There is no way in,
it's not physically possible.

270
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:49,520
Doctor, what's it going to do to me?

271
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:52,560
Just keep looking at it.
Don't stop looking!

272
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:54,440
Just tell me.

273
00:19:54,520 --> 00:19:57,960
Just tell me. Tell me!

274
00:19:58,040 --> 00:20:00,680
Amy, not the eyes. Look at the Angel,
but don't look at the eyes.

275
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:04,360
- Why?
- What is it?

276
00:20:04,440 --> 00:20:06,880
"The eyes are not the windows
of the soul, they are the doors.

277
00:20:06,960 --> 00:20:10,160
- "Beware what may enter there."”
- Doctor, what did you say?

278
00:20:10,240 --> 00:20:12,280
Don't look at the eyes!

279
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:14,920
No, about images,
what did you say about images?

280
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:18,160
Whatever holds the image
of an angel ls an angel.

281
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:22,920
OK... Hold this.

282
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:27,760
One, two, three, four...

283
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:32,080
(DOOR OPENS)

284
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:35,240
I froze it!

285
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:38,600
There was a sort of blip on the tape
and I froze it on the blip.

286
00:20:38,680 --> 00:20:42,360
It wasn't the image of an angel
any more. That was good, yeah?

287
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:45,080
It was, wasn't it? That was pretty good.

288
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:47,240
- RIVER: That was amazing!
- River, hug Amy.

289
00:20:47,320 --> 00:20:48,760
- Why?
- Cos I'm busy.

290
00:20:48,840 --> 00:20:50,400
I'm fine.

291
00:20:50,480 --> 00:20:53,120
- You're brilliant!
- Thanks. Yeah.

292
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:54,800
I kind of creamed it, didn't I?

293
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:58,520
- So it was here? That was the Angel?
- That was the projection of the Angel.

294
00:20:58,640 --> 00:21:02,960
It's reaching out, getting
a good look at us. It's no longer dormant.

295
00:21:06,560 --> 00:21:07,840
Plus one positive!

296
00:21:09,880 --> 00:21:11,840
Doctor! We're through!

297
00:21:11,920 --> 00:21:15,760
OK. Now it starts.

298
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:24,560
- Coming?
- Yeah, coming.

299
00:21:24,640 --> 00:21:27,600
There's just...something in my eye.

300
00:21:39,440 --> 00:21:41,920
Do we have a gravity globe?

301
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,560
Grav globe.

302
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:47,680
Where are we? What is this?

303
00:21:47,760 --> 00:21:50,160
It's an Aplan mortarium -

304
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:51,960
sometimes called a maze of the dead.

305
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:53,360
What's that?

306
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:56,120
Well, if you happen to be
a creature of living stone...

307
00:21:59,320 --> 00:22:01,240
Ha, ha.

308
00:22:05,760 --> 00:22:08,160
...the perfect hiding place.

309
00:22:09,480 --> 00:22:11,920
I guess this makes it a bit trickier.

310
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:13,680
A bit, yeah.

311
00:22:13,760 --> 00:22:17,840
A stone angel on the loose
amongst stone statues.

312
00:22:17,920 --> 00:22:19,480
A lot harder than I prayed for.

313
00:22:19,560 --> 00:22:21,640
A needle in a haystack.

314
00:22:21,720 --> 00:22:24,200
A needle that looks like hay.
A hay-like needle. Of death.

315
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:27,200
A hay-like needle of death
in a haystack of, er, statues.

316
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:29,920
No, yours was fine.

317
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:33,600
Right. Check every single statue
in this chamber.

318
00:22:33,680 --> 00:22:35,800
You know what you're looking for.
Complete visual inspection.

319
00:22:35,880 --> 00:22:38,360
One question - how do we fight it?

320
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:40,120
We find it, and hope.

321
00:22:45,560 --> 00:22:48,920
He doesn't know yet, does he?
Who and what you are.

322
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:51,200
It's too early in his time stream.

323
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:55,480
Well, make sure he doesn't work it out,
or he's not going to help us.

324
00:22:55,560 --> 00:22:57,240
I won't let you down.

325
00:22:57,320 --> 00:23:02,080
Believe you me, I have no intention
of going back to prison.

326
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:06,400
Sir? Side chamber. One visible exit.

327
00:23:08,520 --> 00:23:12,080
Check it out. Angelo, go with him.

328
00:23:58,400 --> 00:24:02,160
- You all right?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

329
00:24:02,240 --> 00:24:05,520
So what's a maze of the dead?

330
00:24:05,600 --> 00:24:07,720
Oh, it's not as bad as it sounds.

331
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:10,720
It's just a labyrinth
with dead people buried in the walls.

332
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:13,560
OK, that was fairly bad.

333
00:24:13,640 --> 00:24:18,880
Right, give me your arm...

334
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:20,960
This won't hurt a bit.

335
00:24:22,880 --> 00:24:25,000
- Ow!
- There, you see. I lied.

336
00:24:25,080 --> 00:24:26,880
It's a viro-stabiliser.

337
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:32,480
Stabilises your metabolism
against radiation, drive burn, anything.

338
00:24:32,560 --> 00:24:34,240
You'll need it
when we get up to that ship.

339
00:24:34,320 --> 00:24:35,960
AMY: So what's he like?

340
00:24:36,080 --> 00:24:40,680
In the future, I mean. Cos you know him
in the future, don't you?

341
00:24:42,040 --> 00:24:43,000
The Doctor?

342
00:24:43,080 --> 00:24:45,240
Well, the Doctor's the Doctor.

343
00:24:46,520 --> 00:24:52,080
Oh, well, that's, um, very helpful.
Mind if I write that down?

344
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:55,200
- Yes, we are.
- Sorry, what?

345
00:24:55,280 --> 00:24:58,960
- Talking about you.
- I wasn't listening, I'm busy.

346
00:24:59,040 --> 00:25:00,320
Ah. The other way up.

347
00:25:05,480 --> 00:25:08,800
- Yeah.
- You're so his wife.

348
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:12,280
Oh, Amy, Amy, Amy!
This is the Doctor we're talking about.

349
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:14,560
Do you really think it could be
anything that simple?

350
00:25:14,640 --> 00:25:15,920
Yep.

351
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:20,600
You're good. I'm not saying you're right,

352
00:25:20,680 --> 00:25:25,400
but you are very good.

353
00:25:31,240 --> 00:25:35,000
CLERIC: Can you believe this?
We're hunting statues.

354
00:25:37,320 --> 00:25:39,560
Better than chasing lava snakes.

355
00:25:41,320 --> 00:25:43,680
Actually, lava snakes weren't that bad.

356
00:26:13,400 --> 00:26:16,360
(STONE SCRAPES)

357
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:22,840
Who's there? Is someone there?

358
00:26:25,240 --> 00:26:26,520
Angelo?

359
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:30,000
Angelo!

360
00:26:35,880 --> 00:26:37,440
Christian, is that you?

361
00:26:37,520 --> 00:26:40,120
OVER RADIO: Angelo, come and see this.

362
00:26:45,480 --> 00:26:48,400
- What is it?
- Just come and see it.

363
00:26:49,480 --> 00:26:52,560
It's not a school trip. Just tell me.

364
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:55,080
No, really, come and see.

365
00:27:11,160 --> 00:27:13,720
(RAPID GUNFIRE)

366
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:21,480
Sorry. Sorry, I thought...

367
00:27:21,560 --> 00:27:23,240
I thought it looked at me.

368
00:27:23,320 --> 00:27:25,520
We know what the Angel looks like.
Is that the Angel?

369
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:27,800
- No, sir.
- No, sir, it is not!

370
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:30,360
According to the Doctor,
we are facing an enemy

371
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:32,280
of unknowable power and infinite evil.

372
00:27:32,360 --> 00:27:34,800
So it would be good,
it would be very good,

373
00:27:34,880 --> 00:27:38,200
if we could all remain calm
in the presence of décor.

374
00:27:38,280 --> 00:27:40,640
- What's your name?
- Bob, sir.

375
00:27:40,720 --> 00:27:44,800
- Ah, that's a great name. I love Bob.
- It's a Sacred Name.

376
00:27:44,880 --> 00:27:50,360
We all have Sacred Names. They're given
to us in the service of the Church.

377
00:27:50,440 --> 00:27:53,200
Sacred Bob. More like Scared Bob now, eh?

378
00:27:53,280 --> 00:27:55,400
Yes, sir.

379
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:57,240
Ah, good.

380
00:27:57,320 --> 00:27:58,920
Scared keeps you fast.

381
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:03,120
Anyone in this room who isn't scared
is a moron.

382
00:28:04,160 --> 00:28:05,400
Carry on.

383
00:28:09,800 --> 00:28:12,320
We'll be moving into the maze
in two minutes.

384
00:28:12,400 --> 00:28:16,320
You stay with Christian and Angelo.
Guard the approach.

385
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:27,640
Isn't there a chance
this lot's just going to collapse?

386
00:28:27,760 --> 00:28:31,480
- There's a whole ship up there.
- RIVER: Incredible builders, the Aplans.

387
00:28:31,560 --> 00:28:34,840
Had dinner with their chief architect
once. Two heads are better than one.

388
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:37,720
- What, you mean you helped him?
- No, I mean he had two heads.

389
00:28:37,800 --> 00:28:39,160
That book. The very end, what did it say?

390
00:28:39,240 --> 00:28:43,840
- Hang on.
- Read it to me.

391
00:28:45,680 --> 00:28:47,960
"What if we had ideas
that could think for themselves?

392
00:28:48,040 --> 00:28:50,960
"What if one day our dreams
no longer needed us?

393
00:28:51,080 --> 00:28:55,320
"When these things occur and are held
to be true, the time will be upon us.

394
00:28:55,400 --> 00:28:58,960
"The time of Angels."

395
00:28:59,040 --> 00:29:02,760
OVER RADIO: Hey, Angelo. Christian?

396
00:29:03,880 --> 00:29:04,960
Where are you?

397
00:29:07,840 --> 00:29:10,000
(GUNSHOT)

398
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:16,120
AMY: Are we there yet?
It's a hell of a climb.

399
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:19,320
RIVER: The maze is on six levels
representing the ascent of the soul.

400
00:29:19,400 --> 00:29:21,800
Only two levels to go.

401
00:29:21,880 --> 00:29:25,480
THE DOCTOR: Lovely species, the Aplans.
We should visit them sometime.

402
00:29:26,480 --> 00:29:28,560
AMY: I thought they were all dead.

403
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:31,160
So's Virginia Woolf.
I'm on her bowling team.

404
00:29:31,240 --> 00:29:33,040
Very relaxed, sort of cheerful.

405
00:29:33,120 --> 00:29:37,280
That's having two heads. You're never
short of a snog with an extra head.

406
00:29:37,360 --> 00:29:39,480
Doctor, there's something.
I don't know what it is...

407
00:29:39,560 --> 00:29:41,120
Yeah, there's something wrong.

408
00:29:41,200 --> 00:29:42,280
Don't know what it is yet, either.
Working on it.

409
00:29:42,360 --> 00:29:46,520
Then they had laws against self-marrying
and what was that about?

410
00:29:46,600 --> 00:29:50,960
But that's the Church for you.
Er, no offence, Bishop.

411
00:29:51,040 --> 00:29:54,360
Quite a lot taken,
if that's all right, Doctor.

412
00:30:01,840 --> 00:30:06,280
Lowest point in the wreckage is only
about 50 feet up from here. That way.

413
00:30:06,360 --> 00:30:09,160
AMY: Church had a point,
if you think about it.

414
00:30:09,240 --> 00:30:12,080
The divorces must have been messy.

415
00:30:13,720 --> 00:30:14,720
Oh!

416
00:30:14,800 --> 00:30:16,800
What's wrong?

417
00:30:19,200 --> 00:30:20,400
Oh.

418
00:30:28,280 --> 00:30:29,920
Exactly.

419
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:31,920
How could we not notice that?

420
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:35,240
Low-level perception filter,
or maybe we're thick.

421
00:30:35,320 --> 00:30:36,840
What's wrong, sir? Nobody move.

422
00:30:36,920 --> 00:30:39,840
Everyone stay exactly where they are.
Bishop, I am truly sorry.

423
00:30:39,920 --> 00:30:42,240
I've made a mistake
and we are all in terrible danger.

424
00:30:42,320 --> 00:30:43,400
What danger?

425
00:30:46,280 --> 00:30:48,720
RIVER: The Aplans.

426
00:30:48,800 --> 00:30:50,200
The Aplans?

427
00:30:50,280 --> 00:30:52,080
- They've got two heads.
- Yes, I get that. So?

428
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:54,400
THE DOCTOR: So why don't the statues?

429
00:30:55,960 --> 00:31:00,760
Everyone, over there. Just move,
don't ask questions, don't speak.

430
00:31:05,720 --> 00:31:10,720
OK. I want you all to switch off
your torches.

431
00:31:10,800 --> 00:31:13,600
- Sir?
- Just do it.

432
00:31:17,640 --> 00:31:22,560
OK. I'm going to turn off this one, too,
just for a moment.

433
00:31:22,640 --> 00:31:24,600
RIVER: Are you sure about this?

434
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:26,920
No.

435
00:31:31,600 --> 00:31:33,520
Oh, my God! They've moved.

436
00:31:49,120 --> 00:31:51,080
They're Angels.

437
00:31:51,160 --> 00:31:54,000
- All of them!
- But they can't be.

438
00:31:54,080 --> 00:31:57,240
Clerics, keep watching them.

439
00:32:04,280 --> 00:32:10,040
Every statue in this maze,
every single one, is a Weeping Angel.

440
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:12,000
They're coming after us.

441
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:30,680
OVER RADIO: Bob, come and see this.

442
00:32:30,760 --> 00:32:33,600
Angelo?

443
00:32:33,680 --> 00:32:36,000
Come and see what we've found.

444
00:32:36,120 --> 00:32:39,480
Are you with Christian?
The Bishop said you'd be five minutes.

445
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:42,240
I'm here, Bob. Come and see this.

446
00:32:42,320 --> 00:32:44,800
Where are you?

447
00:32:44,920 --> 00:32:48,960
Through the arch, Bob.
Honestly, you've got to come and see this.

448
00:32:49,040 --> 00:32:50,280
What have you found?

449
00:32:50,360 --> 00:32:52,000
Come and see.

450
00:32:52,080 --> 00:32:54,280
No. What is it?

451
00:32:54,360 --> 00:32:56,360
Come and see.

452
00:33:21,120 --> 00:33:24,160
There was only one Angel on the ship.
Just the one, I swear.

453
00:33:24,240 --> 00:33:26,440
Could they have been here already?

454
00:33:26,520 --> 00:33:29,480
- The Aplans, how did they die out?
- Nobody knows.

455
00:33:29,560 --> 00:33:31,520
We know. They don't look like Angels.

456
00:33:31,600 --> 00:33:33,680
And they're not fast.
You said they were fast.

457
00:33:33,760 --> 00:33:35,920
They should have had us by now.

458
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:38,160
They're dying. Losing their form.
They've been here for centuries,

459
00:33:38,240 --> 00:33:39,720
- starving.
- Losing their image.

460
00:33:39,800 --> 00:33:42,760
And their image is their power. Power...

461
00:33:42,840 --> 00:33:44,080
- Power!
- Doctor?

462
00:33:44,160 --> 00:33:47,560
Don't you see? All that radiation
spilling out, the drive burn.

463
00:33:47,640 --> 00:33:49,880
The crash of the Byzantium wasn't
an accident - it was a rescue mission

464
00:33:49,960 --> 00:33:53,440
for the Angels. We're in the middle
of an army and it's waking up.

465
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:55,160
We need to get out of here fast.

466
00:33:55,240 --> 00:33:59,880
Bob, Angelo, Christian, come in,
please. Any of you, come in!

467
00:33:59,960 --> 00:34:02,800
OVER RADIO:
It's Bob, sir. Sorry, sir.

468
00:34:02,880 --> 00:34:06,080
Bob, are Angelo and Christian with you?
All the statues are active.

469
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:09,960
- I repeat, all the statues are active!
- I know, sir.

470
00:34:10,040 --> 00:34:13,440
Angelo and Christian are dead, sir.
The statues killed them, sir.

471
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:16,600
Bob, Sacred Bob, it's me, the Doctor.
Where are you now?

472
00:34:16,680 --> 00:34:18,680
- I'm talking to my...
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, shut up!

473
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:21,280
I'm on my way up to you, sir.
I'm homing in on your signal.

474
00:34:21,360 --> 00:34:24,000
Well done, Bob.
Scared keeps you fast. Told you.

475
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:25,800
Your friends, Bob,
what did the Angel do to them?

476
00:34:25,880 --> 00:34:28,880
- Snapped their necks, sir.
- That's odd.

477
00:34:28,960 --> 00:34:31,600
That's not how the Angels kill you,
they displace you in time.

478
00:34:31,680 --> 00:34:34,160
Unless they needed bodies for something.

479
00:34:34,240 --> 00:34:37,520
Bob, did you check
their data packs for vital signs?

480
00:34:37,600 --> 00:34:40,120
We may be able to initiate a rescue plan.

481
00:34:40,200 --> 00:34:42,080
Don't be an idiot!
The Angels don't leave you alive!

482
00:34:42,160 --> 00:34:44,760
Bob, keep running, but tell me,
how did you escape?

483
00:34:44,840 --> 00:34:49,000
I didn't escape, sir.
The Angel killed me, too.

484
00:34:52,800 --> 00:34:55,320
What do you mean,
the Angel killed you, too?

485
00:34:55,400 --> 00:34:58,440
Snapped my neck, sir.
Wasn't as painless as I expected,

486
00:34:58,520 --> 00:35:01,160
but it was pretty quick,
so that was something.

487
00:35:01,240 --> 00:35:03,040
If you're dead,
how can I be talking to you?

488
00:35:03,120 --> 00:35:06,360
You're not talking to me, sir.
The Angel has no voice.

489
00:35:06,440 --> 00:35:09,560
It stripped my cerebral cortex
and re-animated a version

490
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:11,880
of my consciousness to communicate
with you. Sorry about the confusion.

491
00:35:11,960 --> 00:35:15,520
So when you say
you're on your way up to us...

492
00:35:15,640 --> 00:35:18,360
- It's the Angel that's coming, sir, yes.
- No way out.

493
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:22,080
- Then we get out through the wreckage.
- Go, go. All of you, run!

494
00:35:22,160 --> 00:35:24,000
- Doctor?
- Yes, I'm coming, just go, go, go!

495
00:35:27,240 --> 00:35:31,400
Called you an idiot. Sorry, but there's
no way we could have rescued your men.

496
00:35:31,480 --> 00:35:34,960
I know that, sir. And when you've
flown away in your little blue box,

497
00:35:35,040 --> 00:35:37,000
I'll explain that to their families.

498
00:35:42,480 --> 00:35:46,840
Angel Bob, which Angel
am I talking to? The one from the ship?

499
00:35:46,920 --> 00:35:48,000
Yes, sir.

500
00:35:48,080 --> 00:35:50,280
And the other Angels are still restoring.

501
00:35:50,360 --> 00:35:53,600
Ah, so the Angel is not
in the wreckage. Thank you.

502
00:35:55,080 --> 00:35:57,040
Don't wait for me. Go, run.

503
00:35:57,120 --> 00:35:58,320
I can't!

504
00:35:59,760 --> 00:36:02,080
No, really, I can't.

505
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:06,400
- Why not?
- Look at it. Look at my hand. It's stone!

506
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:22,920
Well. There it is - the Byzantium.

507
00:36:24,720 --> 00:36:27,840
It's got to be 30 feet.
How do we get up there?

508
00:36:29,120 --> 00:36:32,640
Check all these exits.
I want them all secure.

509
00:36:32,720 --> 00:36:35,360
You looked into the eyes
of an Angel, didn't you?

510
00:36:35,440 --> 00:36:37,160
I couldn't stop myself. I tried.

511
00:36:37,240 --> 00:36:39,120
Listen. It's messing with your head.
Your hand is not made of stone.

512
00:36:39,200 --> 00:36:41,400
It is. Look at it!

513
00:36:41,480 --> 00:36:43,920
It's in your mind. I promise you.
You can move that hand.

514
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:45,480
- You can let go.
- I can't, OK?

515
00:36:45,560 --> 00:36:47,560
I've tried and I can't. It's stone.

516
00:36:47,640 --> 00:36:51,440
The Angel is going to come
and it's going to turn this light off,

517
00:36:51,520 --> 00:36:54,400
and then there's nothing
I can do to stop it.

518
00:36:54,480 --> 00:36:57,080
- So do it, concentrate, move your hand.
- I can't.

519
00:36:57,160 --> 00:36:59,520
- Then we're both going to die.
- You're not going to die.

520
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:02,480
They'll kill the lights.

521
00:37:02,560 --> 00:37:04,320
You've got to go, you know you have.

522
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:06,560
You've got all that stuff with River
and that's all got to happen.

523
00:37:06,640 --> 00:37:08,640
You know you can't die here!

524
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:11,520
Time can be re-written,
it doesn't work like that.

525
00:37:13,680 --> 00:37:16,440
- Keep your eyes on it. Don't blink.
- Run!

526
00:37:16,520 --> 00:37:18,960
You see, I'm not going,
I'm not leaving you here.

527
00:37:19,040 --> 00:37:21,480
I don't need you to die for me,
Doctor, do I look that clingy?

528
00:37:21,560 --> 00:37:22,520
You can move your hand.

529
00:37:22,600 --> 00:37:25,280
- It's stone.
- It's not stone!

530
00:37:25,360 --> 00:37:27,480
Those people up there
will die without you.

531
00:37:27,560 --> 00:37:29,240
If you stay here with me,
you'll have as good as killed them.

532
00:37:29,320 --> 00:37:33,120
Amy Pond, you are magnificent.
And I'm sorry.

533
00:37:33,200 --> 00:37:36,280
It's OK. I understand.

534
00:37:36,360 --> 00:37:38,360
You've got to leave me.

535
00:37:38,440 --> 00:37:40,920
Oh, no, I'm not leaving you, never.
I'm sorry about this.

536
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:43,440
- See, not stone! Now run!
- You bit me!

537
00:37:43,520 --> 00:37:45,360
Yeah, and you're alive.

538
00:37:45,440 --> 00:37:47,480
I've got a mark! Look at my hand!

539
00:37:47,600 --> 00:37:50,880
- Yeah, and you're alive, did I mention?
- Blimey, your teeth!

540
00:37:50,960 --> 00:37:52,600
Have you got space teeth?

541
00:37:52,680 --> 00:37:54,640
Alive. All I'm saying.

542
00:37:57,000 --> 00:38:00,240
The statues are advancing
along all corridors.

543
00:38:00,320 --> 00:38:02,240
And, sir, my torch keeps flickering.

544
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:03,240
- They all do.
- So does the gravity globe.

545
00:38:03,320 --> 00:38:07,680
Clerics, we're down to four men.
Expect incoming.

546
00:38:07,760 --> 00:38:09,480
Yeah, it's the Angels.

547
00:38:09,560 --> 00:38:12,160
They're coming. And they're draining
the power for themselves.

548
00:38:12,240 --> 00:38:15,040
Which means we won't be able to see them.

549
00:38:15,120 --> 00:38:17,480
- Which means we can't stay here.
- There are two more incoming!

550
00:38:17,560 --> 00:38:18,880
Any suggestions?

551
00:38:18,960 --> 00:38:21,040
The statues are advancing on all sides

552
00:38:21,160 --> 00:38:24,040
and we don't have the climbing equipment
to reach the Byzantium.

553
00:38:24,120 --> 00:38:25,920
There's no way up, no way back,
no way out.

554
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:29,560
No pressure, but this is usually
when you have a really good idea.

555
00:38:32,640 --> 00:38:35,240
There's always a way out.

556
00:38:36,800 --> 00:38:38,120
There's always a way out.

557
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:41,360
RADIO: Doctor?

558
00:38:41,440 --> 00:38:45,480
- Can I speak to the Doctor, please?
- Hello, Angels. What's your problem?

559
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:48,080
Your power will not last much longer,

560
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:51,720
and the Angels will be with you shortly.
Sorry, sir.

561
00:38:51,800 --> 00:38:53,040
Why are you telling me this?

562
00:38:53,080 --> 00:38:54,520
There's something the Angels are very
keen you should know before the end.

563
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:58,280
- Which is?
- I died in fear.

564
00:38:58,360 --> 00:38:59,920
I'm sorry?

565
00:39:00,000 --> 00:39:02,680
You told me my fear would keep me alive,

566
00:39:02,760 --> 00:39:05,200
but I died afraid, in pain and alone.

567
00:39:05,320 --> 00:39:08,560
You made me trust you,
and when it mattered, you let me down.

568
00:39:08,640 --> 00:39:10,600
What are they doing?

569
00:39:10,680 --> 00:39:12,680
They're trying to make him angry.

570
00:39:12,800 --> 00:39:16,160
I'm sorry, sir. The Angels were very keen
for you to know that.

571
00:39:16,240 --> 00:39:20,000
Well, then, the Angels have made
their second mistake,

572
00:39:20,080 --> 00:39:22,800
because I'm not going to let that pass.

573
00:39:22,880 --> 00:39:25,480
I'm sorry you're dead, Bob,
but I swear to whatever is left of you,

574
00:39:25,560 --> 00:39:26,400
they will be sorrier.

575
00:39:26,480 --> 00:39:29,200
But you're trapped, sir, and about to die.

576
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:30,480
Yeah. I'm trapped.

577
00:39:30,560 --> 00:39:33,280
Speaking of traps, this trap has got
a great, big mistake in it.

578
00:39:33,360 --> 00:39:35,080
A great, big, whopping mistake!

579
00:39:35,160 --> 00:39:38,600
- What mistake, sir?
- Trust me.

580
00:39:38,680 --> 00:39:41,200
- Yeah.
- Trust me?

581
00:39:41,280 --> 00:39:42,760
- Always.
- You lot - trust me?

582
00:39:45,560 --> 00:39:48,760
- Sir, two more incoming!
- We have faith, sir.

583
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:50,960
Then give me your gun.

584
00:39:53,720 --> 00:39:57,000
I'm about to do something
incredibly stupid and dangerous.

585
00:39:57,080 --> 00:40:00,200
- When I do...jump!
- Jump where?

586
00:40:00,280 --> 00:40:03,160
Just jump, high as you can.
Come on, leap of faith, Bishop.

587
00:40:03,240 --> 00:40:03,960
- On my signal.
- What signal?

588
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:06,240
You won't miss it.

589
00:40:06,320 --> 00:40:08,760
RADIO: Sorry, can I ask again?
You mentioned a mistake?

590
00:40:08,840 --> 00:40:10,040
Oh, big mistake. Really huge.

591
00:40:10,080 --> 00:40:13,200
There's one thing you never put in a trap
if you're smart.

592
00:40:13,320 --> 00:40:17,440
If you value your continued existence, if
you have any plans about seeing tomorrow,

593
00:40:17,520 --> 00:40:21,240
there is one thing
you never, ever put in a trap.

594
00:40:21,320 --> 00:40:23,080
And what would that be, sir?

595
00:40:24,120 --> 00:40:25,240
Me.

